This paper deals with the compatibility issues between XML schemas and queries, which are related to database management and programming languages. Therefore, cs.DB and cs.PL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a logical framework and tool for verifying compatibility issues, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of schema changes over queries, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
